  <front>
   <head>SONNET TO THE MOON.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">glitt'ring colours of the day are fled;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come, melancholy orb! that dwell'st with night,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come! and o'er earth thy wand'ring lustre shed,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy deepest shadow, and thy softest light;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To me congenial is the gloomy grove,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When with faint light the sloping uplands shine;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That gloom, those pensive rays alike I love,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Whose sadness seems in sympathy with mine!</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But most for this, pale orb! thy beams are dear,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For this, benignant orb! I hail thee most:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That while I pour the unavailing tear,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And mourn that hope to me in youth is lost,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy light can visionary thoughts impart,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And lead the Muse to soothe a suff'ring heart.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
